observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the:
(a) Management allocate fund for the expenses to secure copies of the title of the declared real properties and assigned a focal person to who will focus on the requirements needed to enable the immediate transfer of title of the land under the name of the Municipality;
(b) Municipal Treasurer request and assigned personnel tasked to prepare and maintain updated property cards to enable reconciliation with the general ledger balances and the inventory report.

We recommended that the Municipality:

(a) submit a copy of the Annual GPB to the COA Audit Team within five (5) workings days from the receipt of the approved plan and GAD Accomplishment Report together with the required documents within five (5) working days from the end of January of the preceding year for proper evaluation thereof;

(b) reconcile the amount of utilization of accomplishments as per reports of the Municipal Accountant and GFPS-TWG Chairperson;


(c) gather and establish sex-disaggregated data and incorporate in the GAD Database; and



(d) create the  GAD Monitoring and Evaluation (M&E) Team for proper evaluation of the results of the LGU’s GAD PPAs.

We recommended  and Management agreed to:

(a) strictly comply on the required composition of SWMB for proper representation thereof;



(b) provide support for the 9 Barangays to established their own/clustered MRF or  at least composting areas to comply with the Act and ensure proper waste disposal within their respective area;



(c) strictly enforce the garbage collectors to wear their personal protective gears to ensure their safety and protection.

We recommended and Management agreed that the:
(a)Management:

i) create an inventory committee to conduct an annual physical inventory of PPE by type, with the end view of establishing the correctness of the reported balances as well as the existence, condition and custodianship of the municipal assets and submit the RPCPPE not later than January 31 of each year to enable reconciliation with the accounting and property records and correction of verified discrepancies; and 

(ii) allocate fund for the expenses to secure copies of the title of the declared real properties; 


(b) Municipal Treasurer:
prepare and maintain updated property cards to enable reconciliation with the general ledger balances and the inventory report;


obtain copies of the tax declarations of all properties; 


verify the inclusion of all land in the inventory list against the tax declarations obtained and act on any discrepancy noted, determine whether all lands where the buildings/facilities owned by the LGU are built are titled to the Municipality and maintain a Summary List with costs of all the real properties;

Municipal Accountant:

maintain updated PPELC;  and 


coordinate with the Treasury Department for recording the distinctiveness of each lot/land owned by the municipal government; and


d) Municipal Treasurer, Assessor and Accountant exert effort to verify the existence of the title of the declared real properties and secure copies thereof.

We recommended that the Municipality :

a) submit a copy of the Annual GPB to the COA Audit Team within five (5) workings days from the receipt of the approved plan and Accomplishment Report together with the required documents within five (5) working days from the end of January of the preceding year; 


reconcile the amount of utilization of accomplishments as per reports of the Municipal Accountant and GFPS-TWG Chairperson; 





gather and process sex-disaggregated data and incorporate in the GAD Database; and 



(d) implement, monitor and evaluate the adopted GAD Code of the Province of Bataan in the Municipality.

We recommended that:  

LDRRM Officers :
monitor the full implementation of the LDRRMP towards the achievement of the objectives of RA No. 10121; 



b) utilize the yearly 70% Mitigation Fund of the LDRRMF for the programs, project and activities identified for disaster preparedness, prevention and mitigation; 




(c) strictly comply with the requirements of COA Circular No. 2012-002 for the preparation and submission of the utilization report of LDRRM Fund to the Auditor every 15th day of each month for timely review and verification.
